metadata.editComments:
Added melody, changed ii7sus4no5 chords into I6sus2, and changed key to A major.
A and E are both very strong points of resolution in the key of A, which the melody strongly points to. This section even ends on a big Vsus4-V move, which heavily implies an A tonic. Yes, the tonic A is in first inversion, and vi7 chords are present, but A still sounds like the point of resolution to me.
